Filters:
    - filters are used to format the application data.
    - we have two types of filters

        1.predefined filters
        2.custom filters.

predefined filters:

    - the filters given by framework called as predefined filters.

1. uppercase
    - this filter used to convert the lowercase characters to uppercase characters.

2. lowercase
    - this filter used to convert the uppercase characters to lowercase characters.

3. currency
    - this filter used to append the "$" symbol to the numerical values.

4.orderBy
    - this filter used to arrange the data either in assending order or decending order.

5.limitTo
    - this filter used to display the required number of records from an given array.

6.filter
    - this filter used to search the whole array based on user input data.

7.date
    - this filter used to format the date accroding application req.

custom filter:
    - the filters developed by developer based on application requirement called as custom filters.

Syntax.

<h1>{{"hello" | reverse }}
app.filter("reverse", reverse);
function reverse(){
    return function(arg1){
        var data="";
        for(var i=0;i<arg1.length;i++){
            data=arg1[i]+data;
        }
        return data;
    }
}


<h1>{{100 | my_currency:"â‚¹":true}}

app.filter("my_currency",my_currency);
function my_currency(){
    return function(amount,symbol,position){
        if(position){
            return symbol+" "+amount;
        }else{
            return amount+" "+symbol;
        }
    }
}


















